statistics.name: assists
statistics.description: The number of times a player who passes the ball to a teammate in a way that leads to a score by field goal, meaning that he or she was "assisting" in the basket. There is some judgment involved in deciding whether a passer should be credited with an assist.

statistics.name: turnovers
statistics.description: The number of times a player loses possession to the other team.

statistics.description: The total number of minutes played.

statistics.name: assistTurnoverRatio
statistics.description: The average number of assists a player or team records per turnover

statistics.name: rebounds
statistics.description: The total number of rebounds (offensive and defensive).

article.headline: E. Washington 83, Pacific Lutheran 72
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- Collin Chiverton and Cliff Colimon scored 26 points apiece as Eastern Washington held off Pacific Lutheran 83-72 on Friday night. Cliff Ederaine added 12 points for the Eagles (6-5), who shot 57 percent from the field Cameron Schilling scored 18 points, Cameron Reister scored 15 and Kai Hoyt had 14 points for the Lutes (4-4), who play in Division III. After trailing by as many as 18, Pacific Lutheran rallied and closed to within 65-62 on Hoyt's rebound basket with 5:55 left. Eastern Washington answered with a 9-3 run, capped by Laron Griffin's dunk with 2:12 left. Colimon's 3 gave Eastern Washington its biggest lead, 42-24, with 5:24 left in the first half. But Pacific Lutheran scored the last nine points of the half, capped by Terrell Williams' 3-pointer, to make it 42-33 at the break. Schilling scored 11 of the Lutes' first 13 points.
